{"hash":"480f4ca10b1a6c268b201f089515083ddc799c0a","data":{"post":{"id":"67","title":"Introduce and Setup Tmux","summary":"\n<p>Setup and introduce Tmux so that I can use it</p>\n","body":"\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-cheat-sheet\" class=\"anchor-hover\" href=\"#cheat-sheet\">\n      #</a> Cheat Sheet</h2>\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/ec5b0b3833f81eda4192e7632024763638af32fb/68747470733a2f2f6c696e757861636164656d792e636f6d2f736974652d636f6e74656e742f75706c6f6164732f323031362f30382f746d75782d332d312d31303234783634302e706e67\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/ec5b0b3833f81eda4192e7632024763638af32fb/68747470733a2f2f6c696e757861636164656d792e636f6d2f736974652d636f6e74656e742f75706c6f6164732f323031362f30382f746d75782d332d312d31303234783634302e706e67\" alt=\"\" data-canonical-src=\"https://linuxacademy.com/site-content/uploads/2016/08/tmux-3-1-1024x640.png\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></a></p>\n<p><em>Image from <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://linuxacademy.com\">https://linuxacademy.com</a></em></p>\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-enable-256-color-vim\" class=\"anchor-hover\" href=\"#enable-256-color-vim\">\n      #</a> Enable 256 color vim</h2>\n<p><em>From <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://superuser.com/a/1459904\">https://superuser.com/a/1459904</a></em></p>\n<p>First, outside tmux, you need:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell\"><div class=\"code-lang\">shell</div><pre><code><span class=\"pl-k\">export</span> TERM=xterm-256color</code></pre></div>\n<p>in <code>.tmux.conf</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell\"><div class=\"code-lang\">shell</div><pre><code><span class=\"pl-c1\">set</span> -g default-terminal <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>screen-256color<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>And don't forget to source config manually:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell\"><div class=\"code-lang\">shell</div><pre><code>tmux source-file <span class=\"pl-k\">~</span>/.tmux.conf</code></pre></div>\n<p>All above make sure tmux have full 256 colors support.</p>\n<p>And in your <code>vimrc</code>, add:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-viml\"><div class=\"code-lang\">viml</div><pre><code><span class=\"pl-k\">if</span> <span class=\"pl-en\">exists</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>$TMUX<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>)\n    <span class=\"pl-c1\">set</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">t_Co</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">256</span>\n    <span class=\"pl-c1\">set</span> notermguicolors\n<span class=\"pl-k\">else</span>\n    <span class=\"pl-c1\">set</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">termguicolors</span>\n<span class=\"pl-k\">endif</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-enable-true-color-for-vim\" class=\"anchor-hover\" href=\"#enable-true-color-for-vim\">\n      #</a> Enable True Color for vim</h2>\n<p><em>From <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"292083184\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/issues/1246\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/tmux/tmux/issues/1246/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/issues/1246\">tmux/tmux#1246</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/lifepillar/vim-solarized8#troubleshooting\">https://github.com/lifepillar/vim-solarized8#troubleshooting</a></em></p>\n<p>Basically,</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-viml\"><div class=\"code-lang\">viml</div><pre><code><span class=\"pl-k\">let</span> &amp;<span class=\"pl-c1\">t_8f</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span><span class=\"pl-cce\">\\&lt;</span>Esc&gt;[38;2;%lu;%lu;%lum<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>\n<span class=\"pl-k\">let</span> &amp;<span class=\"pl-c1\">t_8b</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span><span class=\"pl-cce\">\\&lt;</span>Esc&gt;[48;2;%lu;%lu;%lum<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>\n<span class=\"pl-c1\">set</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">termguicolors</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>will do the trick.</p>\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-resize-panes-on-keyboard\" class=\"anchor-hover\" href=\"#resize-panes-on-keyboard\">\n      #</a> Resize Panes on Keyboard</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You may just use mouse though</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This assumes that you've hit <kbd>ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>b</kbd> and <kbd>:</kbd> to get to the command prompt</p>\n<pre><code>:resize-pane -D (Resizes the current pane down)\n:resize-pane -U (Resizes the current pane upward)\n:resize-pane -L (Resizes the current pane left)\n:resize-pane -R (Resizes the current pane right)\n:resize-pane -D 10 (Resizes the current pane down by 10 cells)\n:resize-pane -U 10 (Resizes the current pane upward by 10 cells)\n:resize-pane -L 10 (Resizes the current pane left by 10 cells)\n:resize-pane -R 10 (Resizes the current pane right by 10 cells)\n</code></pre>\n<h2>\n      <a id=\"article-border-chaos\" class=\"anchor-hover\" href=\"#border-chaos\">\n      #</a> Border Chaos</h2>\n<p>If I split the panes vertically, the first column of the right pane is overwritten by the border.</p>\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36528777/86424503-536f7e00-bd15-11ea-87ca-91e5edf7c295.png\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36528777/86424503-536f7e00-bd15-11ea-87ca-91e5edf7c295.png\" alt=\"chaos\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></a></p>\n<p>It turns out to be the old problem with MinTTY. As you can see on the top-middle of the screenshot, the border is displayed in full width (2 chars), with introduced the chaos.</p>\n<p>To solve it, inspired by <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"195884671\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mintty/mintty/issues/615\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mintty/mintty/issues/615/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mintty/mintty/issues/615\">mintty/mintty#615</a>, all you need to do is Options → Text → Locale: C (Or any language with sane character width). And the broken vim airline is solved too!</p>\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36528777/86424514-59fdf580-bd15-11ea-9bc0-d5de662a9d5d.png\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36528777/86424514-59fdf580-bd15-11ea-9bc0-d5de662a9d5d.png\" alt=\"fixed\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></a></p>","createdAt":"2020-01-21T13:55:42.000Z","lastEditedAt":"2020-07-10T12:46:29.000Z","image":null,"labels":[{"id":"blog: programing","name":"programing","type":"blog","color":"60b3bc","path":"/blog/programing/"},{"id":"tag: tmux","name":"tmux","type":"tag","color":"1bb91f","path":"/tag/tmux/"}]}},"context":{}}